reviews.review_text: 12-8-89 Grate show. Grate remaster by Charlie. I'm always dumbfounded when I'm the first to review a Miller remaster.
The Other One The Other One cannot be missed.  It's f*cking crazy!

Pair-o-Dice waits After a lackluster 1988..the band tears it up on the road in 89' Nothing really special about the show..but..what you hear is tight solid playing with energy..sound quality is very nice! Charlie you are the man! And have the ear and know how to produce quality from various sources..Give this one a whirl
Looks Like The Other One Yes, TOO is brutal, as mentioned, but also check out the exceptional LLR, with a *smoking* middle jam. They absolutely nail it.

Smokin' Other One Thrilling version, love Brent in this one and the guys just go off while being pretty technically sound (in a good way). Awesome late 80's show, these Forum shows were so solid and fun to be at. Great recordings of all 3 here on Archive.

First Show!!!1!! The NFA had me so confused. I wish I could remember what I THOUGHT the crowd was singing - I went around singing it that way for hours, maybe days. I remember thinking it was some kind of a contest between sections of the Forum.

What a night!
jerry's guitar TURN UP JERRY'S GUITAR! (end of stagger)
My first show too.... What a show for my first...the balloon guy was there dressed as Santa...WOW....

My 1st Show! I was a senior in high school, and my boyfriend introduced me to the Dead. He took me to my 1st show, which was also the 1st time I took mushrooms. It came on strong during the opener, and my legs wouldn't work walking up the stairs to our seats. My boyfriend carried me back out to the hallway and set me down. Everything was yellow, like looking through a balloon. A beautiful girl came over and gave me love and words of encouragement. She told me I needed to dance. After a few minutes we went back in and I danced my heart away. I became a true Dead Head that night.
